Japanese Bought Net 772.2 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-03-16T23:57:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/japanese-bought-net-772-2-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended March 11 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 772.2 billion yen ($9.8 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 0.1 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 2.5 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 774.6 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 38.2 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 18.4 billion yen in stocks, and sold 296.6 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 316.4
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic  at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  